page.content: { {Our area is mostly open space. There {are 3 reservoirs but only one in use. {There are 2 farms one in Carnbee which {is called Carnbee Farm and the other {is to the east of Carnbee farm which {is called Balmonth Farm. There is a {prehistoric building in our area which {is owned by the National Trust of {Scotland it is Kellie Castle. There is {also a closed down railway but is open {to the public on Sundays. There is {one garage on the St Andrews road {which is called Pitkierie Garage. We {have 2 woods in our area they are {called Kittlenaked Woods and Bonerbo {Woods. We also have a Law in our area {which over looks Carnbee. }
